✅ **Fixed** in commit `80cf0ca` — read-only viewer's typed message is now preserved as a `meta.kind:'denied'` chat row before the denial reply.

## Root cause

`server/src/attach.js handleChatMessage` — the read-only guard at the top:

```js
if (readOnly && user !== ASSISTANT_USER) {
  // ...check guest-allowed slash commands + mentions...
  if (!guestOK) {
    // emit ONLY the denial reply, return
    sessionsMod.appendChatMessage(sessionId, denyMsg);
    session.emit('chat', denyMsg);
    return;        // ← user's text NEVER reaches the persist at line 1398
  }
}
```

The user's typed text was silently dropped — not in `rec.chat`, not on disk, not visible to any other attached client. The viewer had no record of what they tried to send.

## Fix

In the deny branch, BEFORE emitting the denial reply, also append + broadcast the user's message tagged `meta.kind:'denied'` + `meta.reason:'read-only viewer'`:

```js
const userMsg = {
  user, text, ts: new Date().toISOString(),
  meta: { kind: 'denied', reason: 'read-only viewer' },
};
sessionsMod.appendChatMessage(sessionId, userMsg);
session.emit('chat', userMsg);
// ...then the denial reply...
```

The chat pane now shows:

```
kkrazy: try sending a message claude    [meta.kind:denied]
claude: (read-only viewer — claude-routing is owner-only. …)
```

## What this satisfies

✓ The denied message persists in `rec.chat` per the cross-device persistence contract
✓ Other attached clients receive the chat event (live broadcast)
✓ The viewer can copy-paste their text out, edit it, retry through a permitted path
✓ Per the user's clarification: "any message not successfully accepted by the chat pane should be preserved"

## What's NOT in this commit (separate concerns)

- **Client-side styling for `meta.kind:'denied'`** — the data is now reachable; a muted / strikethrough / "denied" badge in app.js would be visual polish. Worth a tiny follow-up if you want it visually distinct from accepted messages.
- **Strict-mode case** — that path was already correct. `handleChatPostfixes` runs AFTER `appendChatMessage` at line 1398, so strict-mode-blocked text is already preserved. No change needed.

## Test coverage (`test/bug-19-readonly-preserves-user-text.test.js`, 5 cases)

- Read-only block exists in `handleChatMessage`
- `appendChatMessage` called ≥ 2 times in the block (user text + denial)
- Persisted user message tagged `meta.kind:'denied'`
- Source order: denied user-message append comes BEFORE the denial reply (chronological chat order preserved)
- Negative guard: first `appendChatMessage` comes BEFORE any `return` — prevents future regression

Adjacent regression sweep: **129/129 cases** across bug-19 + 9 adjacent suites (strict-mode, admin-delegation, bug-17, chat-routing, state-update, chat-persistence-contract, fr-47, fr-49, persist-assistant-chat).
